      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EXCESSOR (1) will find this more to his liking after he made his debut with a narrow sixth over 1200m at this track on February 13. Maps well and can play a leading role here. SPEEDY PETE (4) desperate for this trip now fourth-up. Failed to keep up early when sixth over 1000m at Taree. Doesn't have to improve much to take a hand in the finish. MIDNIGHT RHYTHM (2) Graff gelding from Smartypy on debut for the Mark Mason yard. Had the three trials in readiness for this and gets his chance from the inside gate. OUR MIRACLE GIRL (10) eye-catching return over the unsuitable 1000m with a close-up sixth at Tuncurry. Should come on for this and take a hand in the finish.",
